{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc00f6b6b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16359"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"16359"},"text":"§ 16359.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Competitive award of management contracts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"None of the funds authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary by this subchapter may be used to award a management and operating contract for a National Laboratory (excluding those named in subparagraphs (G), (H), (N), and (O) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s15801/3"},"text":"section 15801(3) of this title","children":[],"tail":"), unless such contract is competitively awarded, or the Secretary grants, on a case-by-case basis, a waiver. The Secretary may not delegate the authority to grant such a waiver and shall submit to Congress a report notifying it of the waiver, and setting forth the reasons for the waiver, at least 60 days prior to the date of the award of such contract."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc00f6b6c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/58/tIX/s995"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–58, title IX, § 995","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/914"},"text":"119 Stat. 914","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc00f6b6d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc00f6b6e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc00f6b6f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This subchapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this title”, meaning title IX of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/58"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–58","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/856"},"text":"119 Stat. 856","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this subchapter, amended sections 8101 and 8102 of Title 7, Agriculture, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s5523"},"text":"section 5523 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":", Commerce and Trade, enacted provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s15801"},"text":"section 15801 of this title","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s8102"},"text":"section 8102 of Title 7","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s2001"},"text":"section 2001 of Title 30","children":[],"tail":", Mineral Lands and Mining, and amended provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s8101"},"text":"section 8101 of Title 7","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1902"},"text":"section 1902 of Title 30","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of title IX to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s15801"},"text":"section 15801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
